<br>
You are camping some stuff in pov/pos, BoT, or other nice PoP zone, the mob is pulled, you jump on it, taunt like a madman with all ya have, and you barely save the day by pressing AoE taunt when the enchanter got a resist on slow after tashing.<br>
<br>
You then see paladin and shadow knight who have exactly the same tanking ability as you do, minus a couple hundred hp in the worst case, and on top of that, they have instant aggro. Not &quot;maybe&quot;, not &quot;sometimes&quot;, not &quot;partial&quot;. Total and safe aggro.<br>
<br>
I've grouped with them with my warrior, my cleric, and my enchanter, and the sad truth is, warrior can't even begin to compare in terms of aggro when it comes to hybrids.<br>
<br>
I mean, theres something really wrong here. Why exactly take a warrior when the knights are garanteed aggro?<br>
<br>
They don't out tank us, they don't outdamage us... they out taunt us flagrantly and absolutely. Making warriors less then desirable when you are facing a triple hitting for 716 mob that needs to be seriously debuffed by you. <br>
<br>
3/4 of a warrior... I just don't see how true that is. 1/4 of a parent caster class... That somehow got screwed along the way.<br>
<br>
